div.p:
ITs is not lawfull to doubt but that, at whoſe becke all

 things did preſently ſubſiſt out of nothing, if by the like power in the ſpirituall Sacraments The earthly matter of bread and wine tranſcending the nature and merit of their kinde is changed into the ſubſtance of Chriſt;
                  Commutetur ſeing he ſayes; This is my body, this is my bloud.
